Fix three icon-resolution defects in src/proxyicon.vala (snixembed 0.3.3):

  1. set_icon_pixmap iterates the ARGB->RGBA conversion with i += 3
     over a 4-byte-per-pixel buffer. The first pixel converts in
     place, then every subsequent iteration overwrites the previous
     pixel's alpha with the next pixel's data, producing garbled
     output for any pixmap larger than 1x1. Stride must be 4.

  2. set_icon falls through to the pixmap path whenever
     theme.has_icon(name) returns false, even when the SNI item
     supplies no IconPixmap data. In that case Gtk's
     set_from_icon_name renders the named icon (or its own
     missing-image fallback) and the pixmap branch corrupts or
     crashes that output. Gate the pixmap fallback on a cached
     IconPixmap property with the expected D-Bus type so malformed
     providers do not get queried through the typed Vala getter.

  3. ProtonVPN starts with a missing theme icon name
     ("proton-vpn-sign") and later switches to an absolute SVG path.
     Its unknown IconPixmap property returns an empty string variant
     instead of the SNI pixmap type, which aborts GLib when snixembed's
     generated D-Bus proxy tries to coerce it. The cached-property
     guard prevents that crash while keeping valid pixmap fallbacks.

Reported against snixembed running on i3bar with the StatusNotifierItem
items advertised by flameshot ("flameshot-tray"), Remmina
("org.remmina.Remmina-status"), and ProtonVPN. Flameshot and Remmina
rendered as identical blank squares before the patch; ProtonVPN could
crash snixembed during tray registration.

Upstream: https://git.sr.ht/~steef/snixembed (patches sent / pending).

--- a/src/proxyicon.vala
+++ b/src/proxyicon.vala
@@ -94,7 +94,7 @@
             }

             set_icon_name(name);
-            if (theme.has_icon(name)) {
+            if (theme.has_icon(name) || !has_cached_icon_pixmap()) {
                 return;
             }
         }
@@ -108,6 +108,14 @@
     void set_icon_name(string name) {
         icon.set_from_icon_name(name);
     }
+
+    bool has_cached_icon_pixmap() {
+        var proxy = item as DBusProxy;
+        if (proxy == null) return false;
+
+        var pixmap = proxy.get_cached_property("IconPixmap");
+        return pixmap != null && pixmap.get_type_string() == "a(iiay)";
+    }

     void set_icon_pixmap(IconPixmap[] pixmaps) {
         if (pixmaps.length == 0) return;
@@ -115,8 +123,8 @@

         var pixmap = pixmaps[0]; // TODO: choose the best one

         // Convert from ARGB to RGBA
-        for (int i = 0; i < pixmap.width * pixmap.height * 4; i += 3) {
+        for (int i = 0; i < pixmap.width * pixmap.height * 4; i += 4) {
             var alpha = pixmap.data[i];
             pixmap.data[i] = pixmap.data[i + 1];
             pixmap.data[i + 1] = pixmap.data[i + 2];
